_header: Enok first with a benign cheer
Subjects: pageant verses; occasional verse; chronicles, verse in; Henry VI, return to London, 1432
_description: Pageant verses by Enok and Eli at the return of Henry VI to London, A.D. 1432, in Fabyan’s Chronicle, Part VII, Septima Pars, Henrici Sexti — two stanzas rhyme royal

HarEng766.First Lines:
Ennok first with a benygne cherePrayed God to vphold his
                    prosperitieAnd that noon Enymyes haue of the powereNor that noo Child
                    of false Inyquytie…
HarEng766.Last Lines:
…And specially among kynges alleIn Enymyes handes that thou
                    neuer fall
